 <span class="text-sm text-blue-400 font-semibold uppercase tracking-wider">Comparison Guide · Updated April 2026</span>
 <h1 class="text-5xl font-extrabold text-white mt-4 mb-6 leading-tight">TOEFL vs IELTS: Which English Exam Should You Choose?</h1>
 <p class="text-xl text-neutral-400 leading-relaxed">Choosing between the TOEFL and IELTS is one of the biggest decisions for students and professionals moving abroad. Both exams are widely accepted, but they test your English skills in very different ways. This guide breaks down every difference to help you pick the one where you will score highest.</p>
 </div>

 <div class="bg-neutral-800 border border-neutral-700 rounded-2xl p-8 mb-12 shadow-xl">
 <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white mb-6">Quick Verdict: Which One Is for You?</h2>
 <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-8">
 <div class="border-l-4 border-blue-500 pl-6">
 <p class="font-bold text-white mb-2 underline decoration-blue-500 decoration-2 underline-offset-4">Choose TOEFL if:</p>
 <ul class="space-y-3">
 <li class="flex items-start">
 <span class="text-blue-500 mr-2"></span>
 <span>You are comfortable with academic, multiple-choice questions.</span>
 </li>
 <li class="flex items-start">
 <span class="text-blue-500 mr-2"></span>
 <span>You prefer speaking to a computer rather than a person.</span>
 </li>
 <li class="flex items-start">
 <span class="text-blue-500 mr-2"></span>
 <span>You have strong typing skills and prefer a 100% digital experience.</span>
 </li>
 </ul>
 </div>
 <div class="border-l-4 border-green-500 pl-6">
 <p class="font-bold text-white mb-2 underline decoration-green-500 decoration-2 underline-offset-4">Choose IELTS if:</p>
 <ul class="space-y-3">
 <li class="flex items-start">
 <span class="text-green-500 mr-2"></span>
 <span>You prefer a real conversation for the speaking section.</span>
 </li>
 <li class="flex items-start">
 <span class="text-green-500 mr-2"></span>
